Intake outcome ledger

Purpose:
- Public-safe record of local file-handoff scans and how intake affected repository work.

Verification status: current-state memory; verify with the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: disposition ledger for agent-file-handoff intake.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; raw source bodies and private payloads are not included.
Update route: replace stale intake state with the current public-safe scan outcome after active intake checks; submit durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: active bucket scans plus implemented code, docs, tests, and reports.
Next action for agents: verify current bucket state before claiming intake is complete.
Must not expose: raw private files, credential values, deployment handoff values, API keys, bearer tokens, database passwords, or raw private report bodies.

Current intake state:
- Active buckets: `agent-file-handoff/Content` and `agent-file-handoff/Improvement`.
- Active bucket guidance lives in `.uai/file-handoff.uai`, not README files inside the handoff folders.
- Content bucket has no committed source payloads beyond placeholders.
- Improvement strategy reports were reviewed and incorporated where they matched MemoryEndpoints.com goals.
- Accepted outcomes: AI-ready discovery, `.uai` startup handoff, docs-backed durable memory, safe no-op behavior, idempotency, package exclusions, deployment-root handling, live route verification, enterprise Python/testing strategy, MySQL/database planning, MATM strategy, hierarchical memory, timestamp-free retrieval, and system-target guidance.
- Durable memory impact: reviewed docs under `docs/long-term-memory/` and verification reports under `docs/reports/`.
- Active memory impact: typed `.uai` records carry current routing facts, intake outcomes, constraints, progress state, and deep links without calendar dates.
- Deferred outcomes: raw report bodies, citation blocks, generated examples not specific to MemoryEndpoints.com, stale file-tree proposals, incompatible routes, unsupported runtime claims, third-party dependency suggestions, and NeuralWikis branding or public content copy.
- Processed outcome: incorporated for accepted summaries and preserved-to-durable-memory for the durable strategy pointers; rejected-with-reason for unsupported claims, copied public wiki material, secrets, or incompatible runtime assumptions.
- Archive result: processed source-site copies belong in `agent-file-handoff/Archive/` or outside the active buckets; active buckets should be empty or placeholder-only after processing.
- Completion gate: agents must rescan active buckets, verify no README/status/index guidance files are present, and record any kept-active blocker before claiming intake complete.
